cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with natural language processing and semantic change, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of diachronic word embeddings and quantifying semantic progressiveness involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of citation networks involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and the identification of lexical semantic leaders involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the study of socio-cultural change can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
